<h2>Sample: Winter Leadership Training Program</h2><strong>Date: </strong>01/06/2010<p>Sample Winter Program.  Open to all AMC members with preference given to active AMC trip participants. Two evening sessions (Tuesday, April 6, and Tuesday, April 13 from 6:45pm-9:30pm) at AMC, 4 Joy Street, Boston, MA; and one weekend (April 23-25) at a New England location (TBA). Cost is $50 and covers course manual, all materials, lodging, and food (except lunches). Limited to 24.</p><img src="http://www.hbbostonamc.org/trips/symbols/12.gif" align="right" alt="Leadership Training" /><strong>Activity Category: </strong>Leadership Training, Instruction (Skills)<br/><strong>Region: </strong>Massachusetts, Boston Area<br/><strong>State: </strong>MA<br/><strong>Country: </strong>USA<br/><strong>Leader: </strong><a href="mailto:springlead@hbbostonamc.org">Bryan Hall</a> <br/><strong>Registrar: </strong>Online: http://www.hbbostonamc.org/springlead/ <br/>

<strong>FMI: <a href="./login.php?event_id=1">Register Online</a></strong>

<h2>Cardigan Winter Workshop Weekend</h2><strong>Date: </strong>01/29/2010 - 01/31/2010<p>Join us to learn the basics of winter hiking! The emphasis of this instructional workshop will be on individual and group winter hiking techniques, hiking safety, preparedness, heat management, proper use of clothing, nutrition, snowshoeing and non-technical cramponing. This outdoor workshop will be held at Mount Cardigan State Park and includes two days of hiking as well as two nights at the AMC's Cardigan Lodge located at the base of the mountain. The workshop utilizes 5,525-acre Mount Cardigan State Park in Orange and Alexandria, NH. Mount Cardigan (3121') is flanked by subsidiary peaks, Firescrew Mountain (3,040') and Gilman Mountain (2,620'). The trails and terrain are similar to those found in the White Mountains and provide a variety of hiking challenge. Typically we offer five different hikes per day to practice winter outdoor skills and techniques. We also offer some lowland hikes along waterfalls and nature trails at the base of the mountain, as well as a self-arrest demo on Saturday afternoon and a backpacking stove demo on Sunday. The $95 fee is payable by Paypal or check. Cost includes Saturday and Sunday breakfasts and lunches, Saturday appetizers and Saturday dinner, as well as two nights lodging. Please Register Online at the link below and we'll send payment option details.</p><img src="http://www.hbbostonamc.org/trips/symbols/11.gif" align="right" alt="Instruction (Skills)" /><strong>Activity Category: </strong>Instruction (Skills), Hiking<br/><strong>Location: </strong>Cardigan Lodge<br/><strong>Region: </strong>New Hampshire, Lakes Region<br/><strong>State: </strong>NH<br/><strong>Country: </strong>USA<br/><strong>Leader: </strong><a href="mailto:psjones10@yahoo.com">Phil Jones</a> 617-275-3172<br/>

<strong>FMI: <a href="./login.php?event_id=2">Register Online</a></strong>

<hr/><div align="right"><a style="color:#cccccc;" name="24908" href="http://www.hbbostonamc.org/trips.php#24908">24908</a></div><h2>Wildcats Ridge Traverse (A3B)</h2><strong>Date: </strong>02/06/2010 - 02/07/2010<p>Joint HB/YM hike. This is an intermediate level backpack for experienced winter hikers. Prior winter camping experience and full winter gear required. Limited to six participants. Register with L Reji James (jreji@yahoo.com/617-335-7416) or L Larry Takiff (larrytakiff@yahoo.com).</p><img src="http://www.hbbostonamc.org/trips/symbols/10.gif" align="right" alt="Hiking" /><strong>Activity Category: </strong>Hiking, Hiking<br/><strong>Region: </strong>New Hampshire, White Mountains<br/><strong>State: </strong>NH<br/><strong>Country: </strong>USA<br/><strong>Leader: </strong><a href="mailto:jreji@yahoo.com">Reji James</a>
<br/>

<strong>FMI: <a href="./login.php?event_id=3">Register Online</a></strong>

<hr/><div align="right"><a style="color:#cccccc;" name="24056" href="http://www.hbbostonamc.org/trips.php#24056">24056</a></div><h2>Jefferson (A2B)</h2><strong>Date: </strong>02/06/2010<p>Full winter gear for this epic above treeline trip. Route will depend on conditions. Can be combined with Ls Sun hike, Contact L Joe about accommodations ($9/person/night).</p><img src="http://www.hbbostonamc.org/trips/symbols/10.gif" align="right" alt="Hiking" /><strong>Activity Category: </strong>Hiking, Hiking<br/><strong>Region: </strong>New Hampshire, White Mountains<br/><strong>State: </strong>NH<br/><strong>Country: </strong>USA<br/><strong>Leader: </strong><a href="mailto:jcomuzzi@kateharper.com">Joe Comuzzi</a> 978-448-9837, <a href="mailto:junemackenzie@verizon.net">June Mackenzie</a> 781-932-1071 (before 9 PM) <br/><strong>Co-Leader: </strong><a href="mailto:rknudsen@rcn.com">Bob Knudsen</a> 781-491-0598<br/><strong>Trip Difficulty: </strong>A2B
<br/>

<strong>FMI: <a href="./login.php?event_id=4">Register Online</a></strong>

<hr/><div align="right"><a style="color:#cccccc;" name="24252" href="http://www.hbbostonamc.org/trips.php#24252">24252</a></div><h2>Mount Pierce/Mizpah Winter Backpack/Camp (C3B)</h2><strong>Date: </strong>02/06/2010 - 02/07/2010<p>Experience the ins and outs of winter camping with lots of support and only moderate exertion on this one-night instructional backpack. We will meet up at the AMC Highland Center to check packs and equipment. We will then travel on the beautiful Crawford Path, the oldest continuously maintained footpath in the United States, to tent camp at the Nauman Tentsite. The tentsite is next to AMC's Mizpah Hut (closed in winter). Conditions permitting, we will summit Mount Pierce. The trip comprises approximately seven miles of hiking and 2,700' of elevation gain (the hike up to camp represents 2,100' of this). Registered participants will receive detailed trip information, gear requirements and directions. Prior participation on a backpacking trip is recommended.</p><img src="http://www.hbbostonamc.org/trips/symbols/1.gif" align="right" alt="Backpacking" /><strong>Activity Category: </strong>Backpacking, Hiking<br/><strong>Location: </strong>Crawford Notch<br/><strong>Region: </strong>New Hampshire, White Mountains<br/><strong>State: </strong>NH<br/><strong>Country: </strong>USA<br/><strong>Leader: </strong>Mitch Silverman <br/><strong>Co-Leader: </strong>Alex Nedzel , Dan Westerberg <br/><strong>Registrar: </strong>Alex Nedzel 781-862-7823 (before 10:00pm) <br/><strong>Trip Difficulty: </strong>C3B
<br/>

<strong>FMI: <a href="./login.php?event_id=5">Register Online</a></strong>

<hr/><div align="right"><a style="color:#cccccc;" name="24057" href="http://www.hbbostonamc.org/trips.php#24057">24057</a></div><h2>Eisenhower (A2B)</h2><strong>Date: </strong>02/07/2010<p>Full winter gear for this slightly easier above-treeline trip. Route will depend on conditions. May be combined with L's Saturday hike. Contact L Joe about accommodations ($9/per person per night).</p><img src="http://www.hbbostonamc.org/trips/symbols/10.gif" align="right" alt="Hiking" /><strong>Activity Category: </strong>Hiking, Hiking<br/><strong>Region: </strong>New Hampshire, White Mountains<br/><strong>State: </strong>NH<br/><strong>Country: </strong>USA<br/><strong>Leader: </strong><a href="mailto:jcomuzzi@kateharper.com">Joe Comuzzi</a> 978-448-9837, <a href="mailto:mackenzie@verizon.net">June Mackenzie</a> 781-932-1071 (Before 9:00pm) <br/><strong>Co-Leader: </strong><a href="mailto:rknudsen@rcn.com">Bob Knudsen</a> 781-491-0598
<br/>

<strong>FMI: <a href="./login.php?event_id=6">Register Online</a></strong>

<hr/><div align="right"><a style="color:#cccccc;" name="23452" href="http://www.hbbostonamc.org/trips.php#23452">23452</a></div><h2>Happy Valentine's Day & President's Day Long Weekend</h2><strong>Date: </strong>02/13/2010 - 02/15/2010<p>Get your snowshoes, crampons, winter sleeping bag and enjoy the snow-covered scenery during the day and friendly conversation each evening in the rustic High Cabin just below treeline. Weather permitting, we will summit Mt. Cardigan, Firescrew Mtn, Rimrock, South Peak and Mt. Orange. $95 per person includes lodging, dinners, breakfasts and gratuity to cabin caretaker. Please start your trip application at http://ashearer.com/personal/trips/register.php?tp=2010-02-HighCabin. One of the Leaders will follow up with you to complete the trip registration.</p><img src="http://www.hbbostonamc.org/trips/symbols/10.gif" align="right" alt="Hiking" /><strong>Activity Category: </strong>Hiking, Photography<br/><strong>Location: </strong>Mt. Cardigan High Cabin<br/><strong>Region: </strong>New Hampshire, Lakes Region<br/><strong>State: </strong>NH<br/><strong>Country: </strong>USA<br/><strong>Leader: </strong>Joan Wu <br/><strong>Co-Leader: </strong>Cliff Chambers <br/><strong>Registrar: </strong><a href="mailto:kelcon108@yahoo.com">w/ CL. Kellie Connelly</a> 781-648-0170 (before 9 PM) <br/><strong>Trip Difficulty: </strong>Strenuous [B3C]<br/>

<strong>FMI: <a href="./login.php?event_id=2">Register Online</a></strong>

<hr/><div align="right"><a style="color:#cccccc;" name="24467" href="http://www.hbbostonamc.org/trips.php#24467">24467</a></div><h2>Mount Liberty (B2B)</h2><strong>Date: </strong>02/13/2010<p>Lead a life of Liberty for just one day. Eight miles, 3,250' elevation gain.</p><img src="http://www.hbbostonamc.org/trips/symbols/10.gif" align="right" alt="Hiking" /><strong>Activity Category: </strong>Hiking, Hiking<br/><strong>Region: </strong>New Hampshire, White Mountains<br/><strong>State: </strong>NH<br/><strong>Country: </strong>USA<br/><strong>Leader: </strong><a href="mailto:ejabel@gmail.com">Erik Abel</a> <br/><strong>Co-Leader: </strong><a href="mailto:kevin_fredette@comcast.ne">Kevin Fredette</a> <br/><strong>Registrar: </strong><a href="mailto:kevin_fredette@comcast.ne">Kevin Fredette</a> <hr/><div align="right"><a style="color:#cccccc;" name="24877" href="http://www.hbbostonamc.org/trips.php#24877">24877</a></div><h2>Backpack to Mount Jefferson</h2><strong>Date: </strong>02/13/2010 - 02/14/2010<p>Join us for a overnight adventure to Mount Jefferson. We'll start early on Saturday morning to the summit of Mount Jefferson, starting at Lowe's Path (a 4,269' elevation gain in 6.2 miles). On Saturday night, we'll camp and cook at The Perch shelter and hike down Sunday morning. For experienced winter backpackers only. 12.4-mile trip total. Register Online with the form below or contact Ls via email.</p><img src="http://www.hbbostonamc.org/trips/symbols/1.gif" align="right" alt="Backpacking" /><strong>Activity Category: </strong>Backpacking, Hiking<br/><strong>Region: </strong>New Hampshire, White Mountains<br/><strong>State: </strong>NH<br/><strong>Country: </strong>USA<br/><strong>Leader: </strong><a href="mailto:julielepage88@gmail.com">Julie LePage</a> , <a href="mailto:jim.shelhamer@alum.rpi.edu">Jim Shelhamer</a> <br/><strong>Trip Difficulty: </strong>strenuous<br/>

<strong>FMI: <a href="./login.php?event_id=3">Register Online</a></strong>

<hr/><div align="right"><a style="color:#cccccc;" name="24784" href="http://www.hbbostonamc.org/trips.php#24784">24784</a></div><h2>Greenland Expedition Slideshow</h2><strong>Date: </strong>02/16/2010<p>2009 Greenland Expedition. Climbing, Climate Research, and a bit of Arctic Sailing. Join Sean Mackay for a slide show presentation explaining how he and a few guys that didn't know much about climbing, and even less about about sailing, managed to pull off a sail-powered climbing expedition from Uruguay to western Greenland's highest peak. Sean and a small team of glaciologist, amateur climbers and some random folks picked up along the way spent a summer in the arctic on a small sailboat monitoring glaciers, installing scientific instrumentation, getting stuck in ice, getting lost, getting found, getting up mountains, getting into trouble, getting out of trouble and having a good time. Join us at Joy Street to see Sean's spectacular photos and hear more about their epic journey. Doors open at 6:30pm, slide show begins at 7:00pm. Free admission. AMC Auditorium, 4 Joy Street, Boston, MA. Brought to you by the Boston Chapter Slide Show Series.</p><img src="http://www.hbbostonamc.org/trips/symbols/29.gif" align="right" alt="Photography" /><strong>Activity Category: </strong>Photography, Climbing/Mountaineering<br/><strong>Location: </strong>AMC Auditorium 4 Joy St.<br/><strong>Region: </strong>Massachusetts, Boston Area<br/><strong>State: </strong>MA<br/><strong>Country: </strong>USA<br/><strong>Leader: </strong><a href="mailto:julielepage88@gmail.com">Julie LePage</a> <hr/><div align="right"><a style="color:#cccccc;" name="25085" href="http://www.hbbostonamc.org/trips.php#25085">25085</a></div><h2>Vermont Snowshoe - Pico (B3B)</h2><strong>Date: </strong>02/20/2010<p>Showshoe along Vermont's Long Trail to one of the most scenic peaks in the Western Hemisphere. This will be a challenging trip in a land where reckless conduct may still be legal. Snowshoes and appropriate attire required. About seven miles and 1600' elevation gain.</p><img src="http://www.hbbostonamc.org/trips/symbols/23.gif" align="right" alt="Snowshoeing" /><strong>Activity Category: </strong>Snowshoeing, Hiking<br/><strong>Region: </strong>Vermont, Green Mountains<br/><strong>State: </strong>VT<br/><strong>Country: </strong>USA<br/><strong>Leader: </strong><a href="mailto:markwarren@mmwarren.com">Mark Warren</a> 617-233-1520<br/><strong>Co-Leader: </strong>Bob Knudsen , Joyce Horrigan <br/><strong>Registrar: </strong><a href="mailto:MarkWarren@mmwarren.com">Mark Warren</a> 617-233-1520<br/><strong>Trip Difficulty: </strong>B3B<hr/><div align="right"><a style="color:#cccccc;" name="24717" href="http://www.hbbostonamc.org/trips.php#24717">24717</a></div><h2>Mt. Jackson and Maybe Webster (B3B)</h2><strong>Date: </strong>03/05/2010 - 03/07/2010<p>(Joint YM/HB trip).Approx. 6.5 mi, 2500 ft. elev. gain. A fun filled weekend in a cozy cabin minutes away from the trailhead! Join us for an epic attempt of Mt Jackson and if the group and trail conditions permit - finish the loop to Webster too. A shorter hike Sun. on the way home. Cost for two nights $35 plus cost of shared food.</p><img src="http://www.hbbostonamc.org/trips/symbols/10.gif" align="right" alt="Hiking" /><strong>Activity Category: </strong>Hiking, Hiking<br/><strong>Region: </strong>New Hampshire, North Country<br/><strong>State: </strong>NH<br/><strong>Country: </strong>USA<br/><strong>Leader: </strong><a href="mailto:silvia@hikebulgaria.com">Silvia Dubinsky</a> , Rich Gambale <hr/><div align="right"><a style="color:#cccccc;" name="23995" href="http://www.hbbostonamc.org/trips.php#23995">23995</a></div><h2>Osceolas</h2><strong>Date: </strong>03/06/2010<p>This day hike to Osceola and East Osceola requires full winter gear and some winter hiking experience. Expect steep terrain that may require both snowshoes and crampons.</p><img src="http://www.hbbostonamc.org/trips/symbols/10.gif" align="right" alt="Hiking" /><strong>Activity Category: </strong>Hiking, Hiking<br/><strong>Region: </strong>New Hampshire, White Mountains<br/><strong>State: </strong>NH<br/><strong>Country: </strong>USA<br/><strong>Leader: </strong><a href="mailto:basch247@gmail.com">Robert Asch</a> <br/><strong>Co-Leader: </strong><a href="mailto:barbaraamoroso@yahoo.com">Barbara Amoroso</a> , <a href="mailto:junemackenzie@verizon.net">June Mackenzie</a> <br/><strong>Trip Difficulty: </strong>B2B<hr/><div align="right"><a style="color:#cccccc;" name="24455" href="http://www.hbbostonamc.org/trips.php#24455">24455</a></div><h2>Mount Adams Backpack (A3A)</h2><strong>Date: </strong>03/13/2010 - 03/14/2010<p>Join us for a challenging winter adventure! Overnight at RMC hut (Crag Camp, $12). Full winter above-treeline gear and experience required. Early start Saturday makes Friday night stay in NH desirable.</p><img src="http://www.hbbostonamc.org/trips/symbols/10.gif" align="right" alt="Hiking" /><strong>Activity Category: </strong>Hiking<br/><strong>Region: </strong>New Hampshire, White Mountains<br/><strong>State: </strong>NH<br/><strong>Country: </strong>USA<br/><strong>Leader: </strong>Larry Takiff <br/><strong>Registrar: </strong>L Kevin Fredette 978-475-8912 (Before 9:00pm) <hr/><div align="right"><a style="color:#cccccc;" name="25107" href="http://www.hbbostonamc.org/trips.php#25107">25107</a></div><h2>Carrigain by Day (AA2A)</h2><strong>Date: </strong>03/20/2010<p>Join us for a day hike to one of NH's more difficult-to-reach winter 4,000'ers. Take advantage of the long winter daylight and good company on the last winter weekend of the year. Enjoy some of the finer views of the White Mountains if the weather cooperates. Post-hike dinner likely. Full winter gear required.</p><img src="http://www.hbbostonamc.org/trips/symbols/10.gif" align="right" alt="Hiking" /><strong>Activity Category: </strong>Hiking, Hiking<br/><strong>Region: </strong>New Hampshire, White Mountains<br/><strong>State: </strong>NH<br/><strong>Country: </strong>USA<br/><strong>Leader: </strong><a href="mailto:jim.shelhamer@alum.rpi.edu">Jim Shelhamer</a> <br/><strong>Co-Leader: </strong><a href="mailto:cgaudette2000@yahoo.com">Chris Gaudette</a> <br/><strong>Registrar: </strong><a href="mailto:cgaudette2000@yahoo.com">Chris Gaudette</a> <br/><strong>Trip Difficulty: </strong>AA2A<hr/><div align="right"><a style="color:#cccccc;" name="25531" href="http://www.hbbostonamc.org/trips.php#25531">25531</a></div>

<h2>Boston Chapter Spring Leadership Program</h2><strong>Date: </strong>04/06/2010<p>For those interested in organizing and leading Boston Chapter trips and events. This program qualifies participants to co-lead trips for Hiking/Backpacking, Intro, Bike, Ski, Young Members, Forty +, Paddling and other Boston committees. Topics include trip planning and trip organization, safety, leadership styles, and group dynamics. Role plays and group situations emphasize experimental learning and decision-making skills. Open to all AMC members with preference given to active AMC trip participants. Two evening sessions (Tuesday, April 6, and Tuesday, April 13 from 6:45pm-9:30pm) at AMC, 4 Joy Street, Boston, MA; and one weekend (April 23-25) at a New England location (TBA). Cost is $50 and covers course manual, all materials, lodging, and food (except lunches). Limited to 24.</p><img src="http://www.hbbostonamc.org/trips/symbols/12.gif" align="right" alt="Leadership Training" /><strong>Activity Category: </strong>Leadership Training, Instruction (Skills)<br/><strong>Region: </strong>Massachusetts, Boston Area<br/><strong>State: </strong>MA<br/><strong>Country: </strong>USA<br/><strong>Leader: </strong><a href="mailto:springlead@hbbostonamc.org">Bryan Hall</a> <br/><strong>Registrar: </strong>Online: http://www.hbbostonamc.org/springlead/ <br/>

<strong>FMI: <a href="./login.php?event_id=4">Register Online</a></strong>

<hr/><div align="right"><a style="color:#cccccc;" name="24331" href="http://www.hbbostonamc.org/trips.php#24331">24331</a></div><h2>Boston Chapter: Spring 2010 Beginner Hiking Program</h2><strong>Date: </strong>04/20/2010<p>Series of five different lectures on Tuesday evenings from 6:30-9:00pm on April 20th and 27th, and May 4th, 11th and 18th at Cabot Auditorium, AMC, 5 Joy Street, Boston, MA. The program of Lectures, Demos and Guided Hikes are designed to introduce beginners to safe enjoyment of the outdoors. Lectures cover equipment, clothing, safety, weather, nutrition, above-treeline hiking, backpacking and other topics. Lectures will demonstrate equipment and participants can interact with experienced hike leaders. First four nights cover general and day hiking topics; May 18th lecture focuses on backpacking. This program includes a number of weekend day hikes to practice skills and gain experience. An intensive weekend of day hiking at Cardigan Lodge and a backpack weekend reserved for program participants available at additional cost. More information and registration at website. $45 for members, $50 for non-members in advance, $50/$55 at the door.</p><img src="http://www.hbbostonamc.org/trips/symbols/11.gif" align="right" alt="Instruction (Skills)" /><strong>Activity Category: </strong>Instruction (Skills), Hiking<br/><strong>Location: </strong>Boston<br/><strong>Region: </strong>Massachusetts, Boston Area<br/><strong>State: </strong>MA<br/><strong>Country: </strong>USA<br/><strong>Leader: </strong><a href="mailto:rknudsen@rcn.com">Bob Knudsen</a> , <a href="mailto:springhb@aol.com">George Marlette</a> 508-789-9855<br/><strong>Registrar: </strong>http://www.hbbostonamc.org/index.php/Table/Spring/ <br/>

<strong>FMI: <a href="./login.php?event_id=5">Register Online</a></strong>

<hr/><div align="right"><a style="color:#cccccc;" name="25549" href="http://www.hbbostonamc.org/trips.php#25549">25549</a></div><h2>Backpack AT from North CT into South MA (B3B)</h2><strong>Date: </strong>05/29/2010 - 05/31/2010<p>Come enjoy the beauty of late spring from this scenic trail over Memorial Day weekend. Please start your trip application at http://ashearer.com/personal/trips/register.php?tp=2010-05-AT. One of the Ls will follow up with you to complete the trip registration.</p><img src="http://www.hbbostonamc.org/trips/symbols/1.gif" align="right" alt="Backpacking" /><strong>Activity Category: </strong>Backpacking, Hiking<br/><strong>Region: </strong>Massachusetts, Berkshires<br/><strong>State: </strong>MA<br/><strong>Country: </strong>USA<br/><strong>Leader: </strong>Joan Wu Chambers , Cliff Chambers <br/><strong>Registrar: </strong><a href="mailto:ronalddimatteo@netscape.net">w/ CL Ron DiMatteo</a> 617-364-8204<br/><strong>Trip Difficulty: </strong>Strenuous<br/>

<strong>FMI: <a href="./login.php?event_id=5">Register Online</a></strong>

<hr/><div align="right"><a style="color:#cccccc;" name="25608" href="http://www.hbbostonamc.org/trips.php#25608">25608</a></div><h2>Foliage Hiking with Full AMC Cardigan Lodge Service (B3C)</h2><strong>Date: </strong>10/09/2010 - 10/11/2010<p>Perfect for adventurous individuals, groups of friends or new members that love comfortable accommodations. Join Ls to treeless summits (Firescrew, Cardigan, SouthPeak, RimRock, Gilbert) with panoramas of MA's Monadnock, NH's White Mountains, VT's Camel's Hump, and ME's Pleasant Mountain. Cost is $150/pp and includes two nights lodging, two dinners, two breakfasts, two days trail lunch, NH lodging tax and gratuity to the crew. Please start your trip application at http://ashearer.com/personal/trips/register.php?tp=2010-10-Cardigan. One of the Ls will follow up with you to complete the trip registration.</p><img src="http://www.hbbostonamc.org/trips/symbols/10.gif" align="right" alt="Hiking" /><strong>Activity Category: </strong>Hiking, Leadership Training<br/><strong>Region: </strong>New Hampshire, Lakes Region<br/><strong>State: </strong>NH<br/><strong>Country: </strong>USA<br/><strong>Leader: </strong>Joan Wu Chambers , Cliff Chambers , Don Provencher <br/><strong>Registrar: </strong><a href="mailto:mo-mac@lycos.com">w/ CL Maureen McCauley</a> 781-572-7494<br/><strong>Trip Difficulty: </strong>Strenuous<br/>

<strong>FMI: <a href="./login.php?event_id=5">Register Online</a></strong>

